      • readDataAsObject

        public <T> T readDataAsObject()
                       throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: ObjectDataInput
        Reads to stored Data as an object instead of a Data instance.

        The reason this method exists is that in some cases Data is stored on serialization, but on deserialization the actual object instance is needed. Getting access to the Data is easy by calling the ObjectDataInput.readData() method. But de-serializing the Data to an object instance is impossible because there is no reference to the SerializationService.

        Specified by:
        readDataAsObject in interface ObjectDataInput
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the object to be read
        Returns:
        the read Object
        Throws:
        IOException - if it reaches end of file before finish reading
